commitResults.messageTitle: Add CustomDate class to store date and modify Tasks to handle it
commitResults.messageBody:
Dates were stored as String and users can input strings that are
not dates. CustomDate specifies the date format to be dd/MM/yyyy
HHmm or dd-MM-yyyy HHmm otherwise it sets it to the current Datetime

Dates are stored in the data file in the format dd/MM/yyyy HHmm by
using the toString method and they are displayed with format using
the display method with format dd of LL yyyy at HH:mm am/pm

commitResults.messageTitle: Add more classes to adhere to OOP principles.
commitResults.messageBody:
Most of the program logic was stored in BabyGronk class, which
did not adhere much to OOP style of coding.

Parser is introduced to parse user input and produce Instruction
that has the correct command as well as args formatted, otherwise,
an InvalidInputException will be thrown.

TaskList is created to store tasks and handle add and delete operations.

Ui class handles the printing of strings to stdout as well as
exiting the program.

Classes were not packaged.

Packaged everything into BabyGronk.

Please remember to organize them into proper packages when you
learn more about packaging.

Files were all under 1 package.

Create several new packages to organise files.
Public methods can be tested for potential bugs using JUnit tests.

TaskList was displaying 0 indexed tasks, but delete command is 1 indexed
so delete wasn't working well with tasks.

Change TaskList to display tasks 1 indexed.

Program wasn't documented properly, hard to navigate through program.

Add simple javadoc to all classes to help explain the code better.

Code violated some format standards.

Format some code and made sure they still pass the unit tests.

If user input too many tasks, search function may be useful to find
a task that contains a certain keyword easily.

Add find method in tasklist that uses string.contains() method to match
input string with the full task name.

Coding standards were hard to maintain and check for especially
since there are so many classes in the program.

Added checkstyle.xml and suppressions.xml that works with build.gradle
to run checkstyle on all the files conveniently.

Also fixed some style errors for some files.

GUI didn't have fxml and selected css implemented

Code did not have assertions to protect program
against bugs.

Add simple assertions to BabyGronk::handleInput

Code was a little hard to read and logic was
messy.

Broke down some functions into parts and created
an enum InvalidCommands for
InvalidInputException.

Importantly, created functions such as
isMarkCommand, isDeleteCommand, isTaskCommand
in Instruction class so that it can be used by
Parser and BabyGronk class statically. Might
need to change this later.

Previously, storage saves the list of tasks line
by line. Now, storage saves the list of tasks
using stream's foreach method line by line.
Add assertions
Refactor code
Modify saveData method in Storage
